---
const cards = [
  {
    headline: "Your phone isn't ringing and you don't know why.",
    body: "You're paying for a website. You're on Google. You've got reviews. But the calls aren't coming in. Usually it's not a traffic problem — it's that nothing on the site tells the visitor what to do, when to do it, or why you over the next guy.",
    linkText: 'Fix website conversion',
    href: '#founding-pricing',
  },
  {
    headline: 'Your competitors keep showing up above you on Google.',
    body: 'The shop down the road has worse work and better rankings. Usually that\'s three things — Google Business Profile setup, review velocity, and on-site service pages. All fixable.',
    linkText: 'Improve Google visibility',
    href: '#founding-pricing',
  },
  {
    headline: "You're spending money on ads and getting nothing back.",
    body: 'Local service ads cost $80–$150+ per lead in 2026. If you\'re sending paid traffic to a homepage instead of a built-for-ads landing page, you\'re lighting money on fire. The ads aren\'t broken. The page is.',
    linkText: 'Fix the landing page first',
    href: '#founding-pricing',
  },
  {
    headline: 'Customers ask for a quote and ghost you.',
    body: "You text back, they don't reply. They say \"we'll think about it\" and book the cheaper guy. The quote process itself is where you lose them — too slow, too vague, no anchor pricing, no easy yes.",
    linkText: 'Build a smarter quote flow',
    href: '#founding-pricing',
  },
  {
    headline: 'Customers keep choosing the cheapest option.',
    body: "When your value isn't explained well, price wins by default. The right service packaging, copy, and quote logic helps customers understand why your work is worth more before they ever call.",
    linkText: 'Package your services better',
    href: '#founding-pricing',
  },
];
---
<!-- PAIN POINTS SECTION -->
<section class="relative border-b border-line">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-5 sm:px-8 py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Sound Familiar</span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 text-[2rem] sm:text-[2.6rem] leading-[1.05] font-bold">
        Sound Familiar?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-5 text-text-soft text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
        If any of these hit close to home, you're not alone. These are the exact problems we built Designed to Elevate to solve — and the reason the Founding 5 offer exists.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      {cards.map((c) => (
        <a
          href={c.href}
          class="card card-hover group p-6 sm:p-7 flex flex-col gap-4"
        >
          <h3 class="text-[1.15rem] leading-[1.3] font-semibold text-text">
            {c.headline}
          </h3>
          <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-text-soft leading-relaxed">{c.body}</p>
          <span class="mt-auto inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[0.85rem] font-display font-medium text-accent group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">
            {c.linkText}
            <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[1.05rem] sm:text-[1.15rem] leading-relaxed text-text">
        We build the path from <span class="text-accent font-medium">Google search</span> to
        <span class="text-accent font-medium">quote request</span> to
        <span class="text-accent font-medium">booked job</span>. Every piece of what we do exists
        to fix one of these problems.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="#audit-form" class="btn-primary">
          Claim My Founding 5 Spot
          <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        </a>
        <a href="#founding-pricing" class="btn-ghost">
          See Founding Pricing
          <span aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- /PAIN POINTS SECTION -->
